'''Ryan Jiro Gravenberch''' ({{IPA|nl|Ryɑn ɣrɑvɛnbɛrx}}; born 16 May 2002) is a Dutch professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[midfielder]] for {{English football updater|Liverpoo}} club [[Liverpool F.C.|Liverpool]] and the [[Netherlands national football team|Netherlands national team]].

Gravenberch began his career with [[AFC Ajax|Ajax]], where he won three [[Eredivisie]] titles. In 2022, he signed for [[FC Bayern Munich|Bayern Munich]], helping them win the [[2022–23 Bundesliga|Bundesliga]]. He transferred to Liverpool in 2023, where he emerged as a focal player in the club’s [[2024–25 Premier League]] win.

Gravenberch played for the Netherlands at various youth levels, and was part of the [[Netherlands national under-17 football team|under-17]] squad that won the [[2018 UEFA European Under-17 Championship]]. He made his senior debut in 2021 and represented the country at [[UEFA Euro 2024]].

== Club career ==
=== Ajax ===
Gravenberch joined the [[Ajax Youth Academy]] in 2010, and worked his way up through the junior levels.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bijlmerenmeer.nl/toptalent-ryan-gravenberch-uit-zuidoost-tekent-bij-ajax/|title=Toptalent Ryan Gravenberch uit Zuidoost tekent bij Ajax – Bijlmer en Meer|work=Bijlmer en Meer |date=10 July 2018|trans-title=Top talent Ryan Gravenberch from Zuidoost signs with Ajax – Bijlmer and More}}</ref> On 7 June 2018, he received the first ever "[[Abdelhak Nouri]] Trofee", which recognises the best talent in the Ajax academy.<ref>{{Cite web |date=8 June 2018 |title=Ajax renames talent award after Abdelhak Nouri |url=https://nltimes.nl/2018/06/08/ajax-renames-talent-award-abdelhak-nouri |access-date=15 March 2026 |website=NL Times |language=en}}</ref> He signed his first professional contract with Ajax that same day, keeping him at the club until 2023.<ref name=":1">{{cite web|url=http://www.football-oranje.com/gravenberch-and-brobbey-sign-first-ajax-contracts/|title=Gravenberch and Brobbey sign first Ajax contracts|date=7 June 2018|access-date=15 March 2026|website=Football Oranje}}</ref> Gravenberch made his professional debut with [[Jong Ajax]] in a 5–2 [[Eerste Divisie]] win over [[FC Dordrecht|Dordrecht]] on 24 August 2018.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2018/08/24/netherlands/eerste-divisie/jong-ajax/bvo-fc-dordrecht/2794387/|title=Ajax II vs. Dordrecht – 24 August 2018 – Soccerway|website=Soccerway|access-date=15 March 2026}}</ref>

Gravenberch made his senior debut with Ajax on 23 September 2018, in a 3–0 [[Eredivisie]] loss to [[PSV Eindhoven|PSV]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2018/09/23/netherlands/eredivisie/psv-nv/afc-ajax/2793980/|title=PSV vs. Ajax – 23 September 2018 – Soccerway|website=Soccerway|access-date=15 March 2026}}</ref> He became the youngest ever Ajax player to play in the Eredivisie at 16 years and 130 days, surpassing the record of 16 years and 242 days set by [[Clarence Seedorf]].<ref>{{cite web |date=23 September 2018 |title=Gravenberch jongste Ajax-speler ooit in eredivisie |url=https://www.gelderlander.nl/nederlands-voetbal/gravenberch-jongste-ajax-speler-ooit-in-eredivisie~ac2d49eb/ |website=de Gelderlander |publisher=DPG Media |language=nl|trans-title=Gravenberch youngest Ajax player ever in Eredivisie}}</ref> Three days later, Gravenberch made his first start for Ajax, scoring in a 7–0 [[KNVB Cup]] win against [[HVV Te Werve|Te Werve]], becoming the youngest goalscorer for the club in the process.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.liverpoolfc.com/news/factfile-all-you-need-know-about-ryan-gravenberch |title=Factfile: All you need to know about Ryan Gravenberch |publisher=Liverpool F.C. |date=1 September 2023|access-date=11 November 2024 }}</ref>

On 25 November 2020, Gravenberch scored his first [[UEFA Champions League|Champions League]] goal in a 3–1 win over [[FC Midtjylland|Midtjylland]] in the [[2020–21 UEFA Champions League|2020–21 season]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.uefa.com/uefachampionsleague/match/2029429--ajax-vs-midtjylland/ |title=Ajax 3–1 Midtjylland |publisher=UEFA |date=25 November 2020 }}</ref>

On 18 April 2021, Gravenberch scored the first goal in a 2–1 win over [[SBV Vitesse|Vitesse]] in the [[2021 KNVB Cup final]].<ref>{{Cite news |date=18 April 2021 |title=Neres' stoppage-time goal seals Dutch Cup win |publisher=AFC Ajax |url=https://english.ajax.nl/articles/neres-stoppage-time-goal-seals-dutch-cup-win/ |access-date=5 April 2022}}</ref>

=== Bayern Munich ===
[[File:2022-07-30 Fußball, Männer, DFL-Supercup, RB Leipzig - FC Bayern München 1DX 3326 by Stepro.jpg|thumb|Gravenberch (left) playing for [[FC Bayern Munich|Bayern Munich]] in 2022 against future [[Liverpool F.C.|Liverpool]] teammate [[Dominik Szoboszlai]].]]

On 13 June 2022, Gravenberch signed for [[Bundesliga]] club [[FC Bayern Munich|Bayern Munich]] on a five-year contract.<ref name=":0">{{Cite web |date=13 June 2022 |title=Ryan Gravenberch signs five-year deal |url=https://fcbayern.com/en/news/2022/06/gravenberch-signing |access-date=13 June 2022 |publisher=FC Bayern Munich}}</ref> The transfer fee paid to Ajax was a reported €18 million, with an additional €5 million in variables.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Summerfield |first=Jude |date=12 June 2022 |title=Bayern Munich director further confirms Ryan Gravenberch transfer |url=https://www.90min.com/posts/bayern-munich-director-further-confirms-ryan-gravenberch-transfer |access-date=13 June 2022 |publisher=[[90min]]}}</ref> On 31 August, he scored his first goal and provided an assist in a 5–0 win over [[FC Viktoria Köln|Viktoria Köln]] in the [[2022–23 DFB-Pokal|DFB-Pokal]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.kicker.de/vikt-koeln-gegen-bayern-2022-dfb-pokal-4774111/spielbericht |title=Tor und Assist: Gravenberch bringt Bayerns Sieg auf den Weg |website=[[Kicker (magazine)|Kicker]] |language=de |date=31 August 2022 |trans-title=Goal and assist: Gravenberch sets Bayern's victory on its way}}</ref>

=== Liverpool ===
On 1 September 2023, the final day of the [[Premier League]] [[transfer window]], Gravenberch signed for [[Liverpool F.C.|Liverpool]] on a five-year contract.<ref>{{Cite web |date=1 September 2023 |title=Liverpool complete signing of midfielder Ryan Gravenberch - Liverpool FC |url=https://www.liverpoolfc.com/news/liverpool-complete-signing-midfielder-ryan-gravenberch |access-date=15 March 2026 |website=www.liverpoolfc.com |language=en}}</ref> The fee, officially undisclosed, was reportedly €40&nbsp;million.<ref>{{Cite news |date=31 August 2023 |title=Ryan Gravenberch: Liverpool agree £34m deal for Netherlands midfielder with Bayern Munich |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/66677935 |access-date=15 March 2026 |work=BBC Sport |language=en-GB}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Joyce |first=Paul |date=31 August 2023 |title=Ryan Gravenberch set for Liverpool medical after club agree £34m deal |url=https://www.thetimes.com/sport/football/article/ryan-gravenberch-set-for-liverpool-medical-after-club-agree-34m-deal-3rm0960f7 |access-date=15 March 2026 |website=www.thetimes.com |language=en-GB |issn=0140-0460}}</ref> On 16 September, Gravenberch made his debut appearance for Liverpool, entering as an extra-time substitute to replace [[Mohamed Salah]] in the 93rd minute in a 3–1 Premier League away victory against [[Wolverhampton Wanderers F.C.|Wolverhampton Wanderers]].<ref>{{Cite news |title=Premier League RECAP: Wolves vs Liverpool - plus six more fixtures - radio & live text |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/live/football/65930748 |access-date=15 March 2026 |work=BBC Sport |language=en-GB}}</ref>

On 21 September, Gravenberch made a lengthy pass into the box to assist [[Luis Díaz (footballer, born 1997)|Luis Diaz]], his first assist for Liverpool, during a [[UEFA Europa League|Europa League]] group stage victory against [[LASK]] in which his side won 3–1.<ref>{{Cite news |date=21 September 2023 |title=LASK 1-3 Liverpool: Nunez, Diaz and Salah score as Reds come from behind |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/66869810 |access-date=15 March 2026 |work=BBC Sport |language=en-GB}}</ref> On 5 October, Gravenberch scored his first goal for Liverpool in a 2–0 win against [[Royale Union Saint-Gilloise|Union Saint-Gilloise]] in the [[2023–24 UEFA Europa League|UEFA Europa League]].<ref>{{Cite news |date=5 October 2023 |title=Liverpool 2-0 Union Saint-Gilloise: Ryan Gravenberch scores first goal in Europa League win |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/67011455 |access-date=15 March 2026 |work=BBC Sport |language=en-GB}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Lynch |first=David |date=5 November 2023 |title=7mcn |url=https://svizanasgrad.me/ |access-date=15 March 2026 |website=Svizanasgrad |language=en-GB}}</ref> Gravenberch started a number of games in the Premier League in October and November 2023 owing to the absence of regular starter [[Curtis Jones (footballer, born 2001)|Curtis Jones]] due to a suspension and then an injury.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Lynch |first=David |date=5 November 2023 |title=Why Jones is not in the Liverpool squad vs. Luton |url=https://www.thisisanfield.com/2023/11/why-curtis-jones-is-not-in-the-liverpool-squad-vs-luton/ |access-date=15 March 2026 |website=This Is Anfield |language=en-GB}}</ref> On 21 April 2024, Gravenberch scored his first Premier League goal in a 3–1 win over [[Fulham F.C.|Fulham]].<ref>{{Cite news |date=19 April 2024 |title=Fulham 1-3 Liverpool: Trent Alexander-Arnold sets Reds on way to reigniting Premier League title bid |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/68810621 |access-date=15 March 2026 |work=BBC Sport |language=en-GB}}</ref>

At the start of the [[2024–25 Liverpool F.C. season|2024–25]] campaign, Gravenberch was shifted by new manager [[Arne Slot]] to a more deep-lying midfield role, accredited to being a [[central defensive midfielder]] in [[Arne Slot]]'s 4-2-3-1 [[Formation (association football)|formation]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Ryan Gravenberch reveals Arne Slot talks about midfield position |date=24 August 2024 |url=https://www.liverpoolfc.com/news/ryan-gravenberch-reveals-arne-slot-talks-about-midfield-position |publisher=Liverpool F.C. |access-date=5 September 2024}}</ref> He won plaudits for his early performances in this new position, particularly for his dominance in a 3–0 win over [[Manchester United F.C.|Manchester United]] at [[Old Trafford]].<ref>{{Cite news |last=McAleer |first=Ben |date=3 September 2024 |title=Why has Ryan Gravenberch become a key midfield cog for Slot at Liverpool? |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/who-scored-blog/article/2024/sep/03/why-has-ryan-gravenberch-become-a-key-midfield-cog-for-slot-at-liverpool |access-date=15 March 2026 |work=The Guardian |language=en-GB |issn=0261-3077}}</ref> He was widely praised by pundits for his performances in this new role.<ref>{{Cite web |date=29 September 2024 |title=Why Ryan Gravenberch finally realized his potential |url=https://worldsoccertalk.com/news/why-ryan-gravenberch-finally-realized-his-potential/ |access-date=26 October 2024 |website=World Soccer Talk |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=Key CHANGE that makes Ryan Gravenberch the world’s BEST DM |url=https://www.msn.com/en-gb/sport/football/key-change-that-makes-ryan-gravenberch-the-world-s-best-dm/ar-AA1sz3lN |access-date=26 October 2024 |publisher=MSN}}</ref> On 27 April 2025, Liverpool beat [[Tottenham Hotspur F.C.|Tottenham Hotspur]] 5–1 to secure the [[2024–25 Premier League|Premier League title]], with Gravenberch providing an assist for [[Alexis Mac Allister]]'s goal.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Liverpool vs Tottenham Hotspur: Premier League preview, team news, stats & head-to-head |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/live/cj3x2ee1261t#Report |access-date=28 April 2025 |website=BBC Sport }}</ref> Gravenberch received praise for his part in Liverpool's successful league campaign and breakthrough in his new midfield role.<ref>{{Cite web |date=19 December 2024 |title=Liverpool: Ryan Gravenberch's new role under Arne Slot |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/articles/c8rjv0x1ry5o |access-date=28 April 2025 |website=BBC Sport }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=2 October 2024 |title=Liverpool 2–0 Bologna: Ryan Gravenberch impresses in Champions League tie at Anfield |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/articles/czrm1lje4ero |access-date=28 April 2025 |website=BBC Sport }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Anfield |first=Index |date=3 October 2024 |title=Gravenberch's Stunning Rise to Liverpool's Midfield Maestro |url=https://sports.yahoo.com/gravenberch-stunning-rise-liverpool-midfield-195000807.html |access-date=28 April 2025 |website=Yahoo Sports |language=en-US}}</ref> At the end of the season, Gravenberch was awarded with the [[Premier League Young Player of the Season]] award.<ref name="RG38" />

On 7 March 2026, Gravenberch signed a new six-year contract with the club, reportedly keeping him at the club until 2032.<ref>{{cite web |title=Ryan Gravenberch signs new long-term Liverpool contract - Liverpool FC |url=https://www.liverpoolfc.com/news/ryan-gravenberch-signs-new-long-term-liverpool-contract |website=www.liverpoolfc.com |language=en |date=7 March 2026}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Paul |first=Joyce |date=7 March 2026 |title=Ryan Gravenberch signs new six-year deal with Liverpool |url=https://www.thetimes.com/sport/football/article/ryan-gravenberch-signs-new-six-year-deal-liverpool-70srp3zdn |access-date=15 March 2026 |website=www.thetimes.com |language=en-GB}}</ref>

== International career ==
Gravenberch was a youth international for the [[Netherlands national football team|Netherlands]]. At the age of 15, he represented the [[Netherlands national under-17 football team|Netherlands U17s]] at the [[2018 UEFA European Under-17 Championship]], helping his team to victory.<ref>{{cite web|title=Italy 2–2 (1–4 pens) Netherlands|url=https://www.uefa.com/under17/match/2024319--italy-vs-netherlands/|publisher=UEFA|date=20 May 2018}}</ref> At 16, he played for the [[Netherlands national under-19 football team|Netherlands U19]]s in a [[Friendly (association football)|friendly]] 4–1 loss to the [[England national under-19 football team|England U19]]s on 5 September 2018.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Ryan Gravenberch signs new six-year deal with Liverpool |url=https://www.onsoranje.nl/teams/185189/speler/23658 |access-date=15 March 2026 |website=www.onsoranje.nl}}</ref>

He was first called up to the senior [[Netherlands national football team|Netherlands]] squad in November 2020.<ref>{{cite news |title=Netherlands 3–1 Bosnia & Herzegovina |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/54952579|work=BBC Sport |access-date=16 November 2020}}</ref> He made his debut on 24 March 2021 in a [[2022 FIFA World Cup qualification – UEFA Group G|2022 FIFA World Cup qualifier]] against [[Turkey national football team|Turkey]]. On 2 June 2021, Gravenberch was named in the Dutch squad for [[UEFA Euro 2020]].<ref>{{Cite news |date=14 September 2021|title=The Netherlands’ full 24-man Euro 2020 squad |url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/4211011/2021/06/01/the-netherlands-full-24-man-euro-2020-squad/ |access-date=15 March 2026 |work=The New York Times |language=en-US |issn=0362-4331}}</ref> Four days later, he scored his first international goal in a 3–0 win against [[Georgia national football team|Georgia]] in a pre-tournament friendly match.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=FIFA|url=https://www.fifa.com/worldcup/preliminaries/europe/matches/match/400155684/|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210122034714/https://www.fifa.com/worldcup/preliminaries/europe/matches/match/400155684/|url-status=dead|archive-date=22 January 2021|title=Turkey v Netherlands game report|date=24 March 2021}}</ref><ref name=":0" /> At the tournament finals, Gravenberch appeared as a substitute in the team's second group match against [[Austria national football team|Austria]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.uefa.com/uefaeuro/match/2024443--netherlands-vs-austria/|title=Netherlands vs Austria|date=17 June 2021|access-date=12 June 2024|publisher=UEFA}}</ref> and played the full 90 minutes in the third group match against [[North Macedonia national football team|North Macedonia]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.uefa.com/uefaeuro/match/2024445--north-macedonia-vs-netherlands/|title=North Macedonia vs Netherlands|date=21 June 2021|access-date=12 June 2024|publisher=UEFA}}</ref>

On 4 September 2023, days after signing for Liverpool, Gravenberch declined a call-up to the [[Netherlands national under-21 football team|Netherlands U21s]] for their [[UEFA European Under-21 Championship|European Championship]] qualification campaign.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Gravenberch niet bij Jong Oranje; Fedde de Jong is zijn vervanger |url=https://www.onsoranje.nl/nieuws/jong-oranje-mannen/80973/gravenberch-niet-bij-jong-oranje-fedde-de-jong-zijn-vervanger |access-date=14 September 2023 |website=onsoranje.nl|trans-title=Gravenberch not with Jong Oranje; Fedde de Jong is his replacement}}</ref> The team confirmed his absence was a choice to "focus on his new club", with national coach [[Ronald Koeman]] and U21s coach [[Michael Reiziger]] condemning the decision.<ref>{{Cite web |date=4 September 2023 |title=Reiziger duidelijk over afmelding Gravenberch: 'Een verkeerde keuze' |url=https://www.vi.nl/nieuws/reiziger-duidelijk-over-afmelding-gravenberch-een-verkeerde-keuze |access-date=14 September 2023 |website=Voetbal International |language=nl|trans-title=Reiziger clear about Gravenberch withdrawal: 'A wrong choice'}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=Koeman deelde 'straf' uit aan Frimpong en baalt van Gravenberch: 'Niet blij mee' |url=https://www.voetbalnieuws.nl/nieuws/35481/koeman-deelde-straf-uit-aan-frimpong-en-baalt-van-gravenberch-niet-blij-mee.html |access-date=14 September 2023 |website=voetbalnieuws.nl |date=4 September 2023 |language=nl-NL|trans-title=Koeman dealt out 'punishment' to Frimpong and is fed up with Gravenberch: 'Not happy with it'}}</ref>

On 29 May 2024, Gravenberch was named in the Netherlands' squad for [[UEFA Euro 2024]].<ref>{{Cite news |last=Davis |first=Callum |date=11 June 2021 |title=Netherlands Euro 2024 squad: Georginio Wijnaldum and Daley Blind retained |url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/5526712/2024/05/29/netherlands-euro-2024-squad-confirmed/ |access-date=15 March 2026 |work=The New York Times |language=en-US |issn=0362-4331}}</ref>

== Personal life ==
Gravenberch was born in the Netherlands to [[Afro-Surinamese]] parents.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://football-wonderkids.co.uk/player/ryan-gravenberch/|title=Ryan Gravenberch|date=2 July 2024|access-date=15 March 2026|website=Football-Wonderkids}}</ref> In August 2025, Gravenberch and his partner Cindy Peroti announced the birth of their first child, a daughter.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Quinlan |first1=James |title=Liverpool midfielder Ryan Gravenberch and partner supported as they issue family update |url=https://www.liverpoolecho.co.uk/sport/football/football-news/liverpool-midfielder-ryan-gravenberch-partner-32301619 |website=[[Liverpool Echo]] |access-date=25 August 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250825062854/https://www.liverpoolecho.co.uk/sport/football/football-news/liverpool-midfielder-ryan-gravenberch-partner-32301619 |archive-date=25 August 2025 |date=18 August 2025}}</ref>

His older brother, [[Danzell Gravenberch|Danzell]], is a former professional footballer.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.elfvoetbal.nl/Binnenland/272634/Ryan-Gravenberch-een-Raiola-diamant-die-wl-bij-Ajax-blijft-Wil-eerste-halen|title=Ryan Gravenberch, een Raiola-diamant die wél bij Ajax blijft: "Wil eerste halen"|website=Elfvoetbal.nl|trans-title=Ryan Gravenberch, a Raiola diamond who is staying at Ajax: "Want to reach the first team"}}</ref>

